description: From Middle English *faxed, from Old English feaxed, ġefeaxed (“haired; having hair”), from Old English feax (“hair”). More at fax.

adjectives.description: faxed (comparative more faxed, superlative most faxed)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Having a head of hair; hairy.
examples: A comet is a ‘faxed’ star, that is, a hairy, a tailed star. But ‘faxed’ got corrupted into ‘fixed’ star during the seventeenth century.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of fax
